article.headline: Austin Peay 74, Tenn.-Martin 58
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Fernandez Lockett and Todd Babington combined for 41 points and career highs to lead Austin Peay to a 74-58 win over Tennessee-Martin on Tuesday night. The Governors (6-6, 3-1 Ohio Valley Conference) briefly trailed early before taking the lead on a jumper by Kyle Duncan to go ahead 9-7 and lead the rest of the game. Babington led Austin Peay with 21 points, all from his 7-of-13 shooting from the arc. Lockett had career highs with his 20 points, six assists and three blocked shots. He also had a game-high 12 rebounds. Drake Reed had 11 points and nine rebounds. The Skyhawks (3-12, 1-4) were led by McClenon Tolliver, with 15 points, and Cleve Woodfork with 15 points and a team-high seven rebounds. Austin Peay jumped to a 36-27 lead at the half and shot 45.2 percent from the field, to the Skyhawks' 36.8.
